  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Taijutsu (Strike)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 12 (Spell Level 6)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 4</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 28 | <b>Successes:</b> 5</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 16 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 32</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> F, Mob</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You make a graceful yet powerful strike, against which the target loses its Dexterity bonus to Defense. On hit, the target seems completely unaffected, but it numb to any physical pain for 1 round. On your next turn, a cut suddenly appears on the subject, dealing 3d6 slashing damage, +1 per level (up to 3d6+15) that bypasses all damage reductions. In addition, the target must make a massive damage save. This attack has a critical of (20, x2).<br><br>The target does not suffer any pain from the damage, even if it dies. If your weapon was not at least of mastercraft +2 quality, it is destroyed beyond repair.</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
